data.title: Lumen Technologies (NYSE: LUMN) stock rises post Q3 earnings report, surpassing analyst estimates. 20 cent EPS loss, $3.08B revenue.
data.description: Shares of Lumen Technologies, Inc. (NYSE: LUMN) surged following the release of its third-quarter earnings report after the market closed on Thursday. The company exceeded expectations on both the top and bottom lines. LUMN stock saw an uptick in response. The report revealed quarterly losses of 20 cents per share, outperforming the anticipated losses of 27 cents per share by analysts. Additionally, quarterly revenue stood at $3.08 billion, surpassing the analyst consensus estimate of $3.03 billion. For more in-depth coverage, the full story can be accessed on Benzinga.com.

data.title: Cloudflare (NYSE: NET) stock rises on Q3 earnings report. Beat Street estimate with 27 cents per share and revenue of $562.02M.
data.description: Cloudflare Inc. (NYSE: NET) saw a rise in shares following the release of its Q3 earnings report. The stock experienced an increase, with quarterly earnings at 27 cents per share, surpassing the Street's forecast of 23 cents. Cloudflare's Q3 revenue totaled $562.02 million. For real-time price updates on NET stock, refer to the stock exchange. Check out more details regarding this news update. Discover further insights on the full story at Benzinga.com.

data.title: Partnership formed by IIP and Nissan Chemical America to distribute nanoActiv® technology for Enhanced Oil Recovery in MENA.
data.description: In Abu Dhabi, UAE, on October 30, 2025, International Industrial Partners (IIP) revealed a new collaboration with Nissan Chemical America to distribute nanoActiv® technology. This groundbreaking technology is known for being the first brine-resistant innovation globally. This partnership aims to market and distribute nanoActiv® to a wider audience through IIP's network.

data.title: Mastercard plans to acquire Zerohash for stablecoin growth with $2 billion deal, enhancing settlement options.
data.description: It has been reported that Mastercard is close to finalizing a purchase agreement worth $2 billion to buy Zerohash, a company specializing in crypto infrastructure. The goal of this acquisition is to strengthen Mastercard's stablecoin and on-chain settlement functionalities.

data.title: Ziegler prices $34M Series 2025 Bonds for Carol Woods retirement center in Chapel Hill, NC.
data.description: Ziegler has happily disclosed the effective pricing of a total of $34,000,000 Series 2025 Bonds for The Chapel Hill Residential Retirement Center, Inc., operating as Carol Woods. Established in July 1972, Carol Woods is a nonprofit organization in North Carolina.

data.title: Nektar Therapeutics will be at the Jefferies Global Healthcare Conference in London on Nov 17-20, 2025. #NKTR
data.description: Nektar Therapeutics (Nasdaq: NKTR) has disclosed that its management will be webcasting their involvement at the Jefferies Global Healthcare Conference taking place from November 17-20, 2025 in London. This announcement was made in San Francisco on October 30, 2025. This move aims to showcase the company's presence at the significant event, providing insights into their contributions to the conference.

data.title: Elizabeth A. Tedesco, MME recognized as a Pinnacle Professional Member Inner Circle of Excellence for music education in Mahopac, NY.
data.description: In Mahopac, New York on October 30, 2025, a notable figure, Elizabeth A. Tedesco, MME, was recognized in The Inner Circle as a Pinnacle Professional Member. She was acknowledged for her significant contributions towards the enhancement of the community through music education and performance. Elizabeth A. Tedesco's achievements in this area have earned her a position in the Inner Circle of Excellence.

data.title: Caroline Camfield named Pinnacle Professional Member of Inner Circle for contributions in Residential Real Estate.
data.description: In Santa Teresa, New Mexico on October 30, 2025, Caroline Camfield has been acknowledged as a standout member of The Inner Circle, achieving the prestigious title of Pinnacle Professional Member Inner Circle of Excellence for her impactful work in Residential Real Estate. Camfield is being celebrated for her remarkable contributions spanned over nearly two years.

data.title: NEXE Innovations reports strong Q1 2026 results: revenue up, positive gross margin, 99% food safety audit score, and strong cash position.
data.description: NEXE Innovations has released its first-quarter 2026 financial report, showing a notable increase in revenue compared to the previous period. The company also reported a positive gross margin and highlighted its robust cash reserves. Impressively, NEXE Innovations achieved an outstanding 99% score in a recent food safety audit, demonstrating its unwavering commitment to ensuring top-notch quality standards.

data.title: INDOCHINO launches Black Friday event on Nov 3rd in showrooms and online, the global leader in made-to-measure apparel.
data.description: A renowned made-to-measure brand is set to showcase confidence, design, and creativity during its upcoming Black Friday event starting on November 3rd across showrooms and online platforms. With headquarters in Vancouver, BC, and New York, the industry leader INDOCHINO is launching this event to offer exclusive deals and promotions to its customers.

data.description: Cloudflare's stock experienced fluctuations following the announcement of their Q3 earnings, which exceeded expectations. Additionally, the company provided guidance that slightly surpassed projected figures. However, it was also revealed that a significant executive has departed from the company.

data.title: Edwards Lifesciences stock rises after beating quarterly calls and boosting 2025 outlook, also announces CFO transition.
data.description: Shares of Edwards Lifesciences saw a significant increase in value on Thursday following the company's announcement of raising its 2025 outlook. This comes after surpassing quarterly expectations. The medtech firm also revealed a transition in its CFO position. The news led to a surge in the stock price, signaling positive investor response.

data.title: Amazon stock surges on AWS growth, exceeding expectations with 20% sales acceleration - Investors pleased.
data.description: Amazon Web Services (AWS) exceeded expectations by achieving a significant sales acceleration, resulting in a growth of 20%. This boost in performance led to a surge in Amazon's stock and satisfied investors seeking growth in the AI Cloud sector.
